      <bioghist id="aspace_a7738e5e71848051d299bce6249181d8">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Hoyt Curtiss Pease was born on June 24, 1911, in New Britain, Connecticut, and was a graduate of the Class of 1934, Sheffield Scientific School, Yale University. While at Yale, Pease was a member of the 150-pound crew squad, assistant manager and manager of the university crew, and secretary and treasurer of the Yale Corinthian Yacht Club. He served as regatta chairman from 1940-1974.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_d79e60fa64f1470e40f9ff85ef4daa90">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of writings, printed material, programs, and photographs compiled by Hoyt Curtiss Pease pertaining to Yale crew.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
